<refnamediv><refname>imshow_segmentation</refname><refpurpose>Display an image with a segmentation mask overlay.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>overlay = imshow_segmentation(image, mask)
overlay = imshow_segmentation(image, mask, rgb, alpha, titleText)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image :</term><listitem><para>Input image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>mask :</term><listitem><para>Binary or label mask.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>rgb :</term><listitem><para>RGB overlay color. Default is <literal>[255 0 0]</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>alpha :</term><listitem><para>Overlay opacity from <literal>0</literal> to <literal>1</literal>. Default is <literal>0.35</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>titleText :</term><listitem><para>Optional figure title.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>overlay :</term><listitem><para>Displayed RGB overlay image.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imshow_segmentation</function> displays a segmentation overlay and also returns the overlay image for saving or further processing.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/baboon.png"));
mask = zeros(size(image, 1), size(image, 2));
mask(80:180, 100:220) = 1;
overlay = imshow_segmentation(image, mask, [255 0 0], 0.35, "Segmentation");
]]></programlisting></refsection>
